<subSubSection id="A00DD3D42BE8962870FFED0997F27A3D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="multiple">
<paragraph id="BF45D83D16BF41B0E28CFF82764A665F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="934B6E8E377FBAA81B960071E217AD10" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution of species.</emphasis>
Locally common between 200 and 2400 m in the Sonora Desert of Southern Arizona, but uncommon and scattered in other semi desert areas of northern Mexico and the United States southwest.
</paragraph>
